        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "The current code in the mysqli driver assumes that the Mysqli class is available.\nIf it is not (extension not installed) an exception is not thrown, and the @ makes the error hid from the normal output. We are left with a blank screen.\n\nThe code should test for the presence of the mysqli class and raise an exception if it is not known.\n\n{code}\n        \/\/ Suppress connection warnings here.\n        \/\/ Throw an exception instead.\n        @$this->_connection = new mysqli(\n            $this->_config['host'],\n            $this->_config['username'],\n            $this->_config['password'],\n            $this->_config['dbname'],\n            $port\n        );\n{code}\n\n\nShould be\n\n{code}\n\n\t\tif(!class_exists(\"mysqli\"))\n\t\t{\n            \/**\n             * @see Zend_Db_Adapter_Mysqli_Exception\n             *\/\n            require_once 'Zend\/Db\/Adapter\/Mysqli\/Exception.php';\n            throw new Zend_Db_Adapter_Mysqli_Exception(\"The extension mysqli is not installed.\");\n\t\t}\n\t\n        \/\/ Suppress connection warnings here.\n        \/\/ Throw an exception instead.\n        @$this->_connection = new mysqli(\n            $this->_config['host'],\n            $this->_config['username'],\n            $this->_config['password'],\n            $this->_config['dbname'],\n            $port\n        );\n\n{code}"
        },
